WEBVTT

00:08.007 --> 00:09.533
<i>Have you been told?</i>

00:09.810 --> 00:13.872
<i>Did you ever hear of the curious,
furious, fidgety year...</i>

00:14.114 --> 00:18.745
<i>...when Santa Claus unhitched his sleigh
and vowed he was taking a holiday?</i>

00:19.620 --> 00:23.784
How do I know so much about Santa?
Well, I'm Mrs. Claus.

00:25.158 --> 00:27.718
It was long ago before you were living.

00:28.695 --> 00:33.599
Not yet Christmas, but past Thanksgiving,
though I can't give you the very date.

00:36.537 --> 00:41.202
<i>Santa got up that morning late,
pulled on one boot, and then, its twin...</i>

00:41.542 --> 00:43.510
<i>...ruffled the whiskers on his chin...</i>

00:43.577 --> 00:45.909
...and sat back down
on the side of the bed.

00:46.146 --> 00:48.581
Great North Star, but I'm tired.

00:48.982 --> 00:49.881
...he said.

00:49.950 --> 00:53.978
Painting wagons red and bright,
sharpening ice skates half the night...

00:54.621 --> 00:57.488
...wrapping presents in ribbons and gauze...

00:58.191 --> 00:59.681
...has worn me weary.

01:00.060 --> 01:01.494
...said Santa Claus.

01:01.828 --> 01:03.887
Crick in my back.

01:04.230 --> 01:05.562
Cold in my nose.

01:05.699 --> 01:08.896
Aches in my fingers and all ten toes...

01:09.603 --> 01:13.471
...and a sort of kind of kink inside
whenever I think of...

01:14.341 --> 01:16.002
...that Christmas ride.

01:16.610 --> 01:19.705
Now, Santa, you just rest yourself
a bit longer.

01:19.880 --> 01:21.644
I've already sent for the doctor.

01:21.715 --> 01:24.116
We'll have you back on your feet
in no time.

01:29.222 --> 01:31.452
No wonder you got the shivers and shakes.

01:31.825 --> 01:35.784
Probably, never got over the case of
near-pneumonia you picked up last year...

01:35.862 --> 01:38.729
...gallivanting around the world
in your open sleigh.

01:38.999 --> 01:40.125
And for what?

01:40.334 --> 01:45.135
Just to deliver presents to a bunch of folks
who don't give a hoot in the first place.

01:45.372 --> 01:46.237
But...

01:47.908 --> 01:51.708
Now, now, Doctor.
It's not just presents, and you know it.

01:52.279 --> 01:54.941
What about all that Christmas spirit
and goodwill?

01:55.182 --> 01:57.844
If you had any sense,
you'd give it up as a bad job...

01:57.918 --> 01:59.784
...and stay home in bed this year.

01:59.853 --> 02:03.847
Come now. If Santa stayed home,
there'd be no Christmas.

02:04.458 --> 02:07.689
Who cares?
Nobody cares about Christmas anymore.

02:08.027 --> 02:09.189
They don't?

02:11.131 --> 02:12.292
Of course not.

02:12.733 --> 02:16.431
Wouldn't surprise me none
if nobody even believes in you anymore.

02:16.503 --> 02:18.733
Now, Santa, don't you pay him any mind.

02:18.872 --> 02:22.274
Nobody cares a hooting holler for you
or Christmas.

02:23.210 --> 02:25.474
By the way, Merry Christmas to you.

02:26.780 --> 02:30.216
Now, Santa, I hope you're not going
to take any of that to heart.

02:30.317 --> 02:32.684
No, Ma. The man's right.

02:32.753 --> 02:36.781
I had that same feeling myself,
but I just wouldn't admit it.

02:37.624 --> 02:40.559
Nobody really cares anymore.

02:40.961 --> 02:42.986
And besides, the doctor says...

02:43.063 --> 02:45.191
...I'm really not up to snuff.

02:45.699 --> 02:48.396
Besides, I'm due for a holiday.

02:49.703 --> 02:52.172
I better call the boys...

02:53.040 --> 02:55.634
...and tell them to cancel Christmas.

02:59.646 --> 03:05.710
<i>Warn the people. Tell the papers
I'm much too tired for Christmas capers.</i>

03:07.254 --> 03:09.120
But Santa, you must be kidding.

03:09.456 --> 03:10.582
But, it was true.

03:10.857 --> 03:14.293
Santa was taking a holiday
and the world would soon know...

03:14.361 --> 03:18.264
...that it was to be the year
without a Santa Claus.

03:18.832 --> 03:23.326
"Did you ever hear
of that terrible year

03:23.804 --> 03:26.466
"Way back before you were born

03:28.341 --> 03:32.903
"When Santa Claus took a holiday

03:32.979 --> 03:36.779
"On the night before Christmas morn?"

03:39.453 --> 03:44.186
<i>"It was a year without a Santa Claus</i>

03:44.391 --> 03:47.622
<i>"A Christmas year so sad</i>

03:48.095 --> 03:52.328
<i>"It was a year without a Santa Claus</i>

03:52.566 --> 03:56.002
<i>"The worst we've ever had</i>

03:56.570 --> 04:00.404
<i>"Santa woke up one day
looking tuckered and gray</i>

04:00.874 --> 04:03.639
<i>"And this is what he said:</i>

04:04.644 --> 04:08.512
"'I could sure use some rest
I'm not feeling my best'

04:08.782 --> 04:11.513
<i>"And he yawned as he took to his bed</i>

04:12.552 --> 04:16.785
<i>"There'll" be a year without a Santa Claus</i>

04:17.124 --> 04:20.423
"I'm sure they won't miss me

04:20.827 --> 04:25.230
<i>"There'll" be a year without a Santa Claus</i>

04:25.298 --> 04:28.632
<i>"Beside your Christmas tree</i>

04:29.169 --> 04:33.265
<i>"And he dept through the day
as the hours ticked away</i>

04:33.373 --> 04:36.673
<i>"And the time was growing</i> near

04:37.544 --> 04:39.478
<i>"And the children, they cried</i>

04:39.546 --> 04:41.571
<i>"They thought Santa had died</i>

04:41.815 --> 04:45.149
<i>"Every eye shed a blue Christmas tear</i>

04:45.786 --> 04:50.656
<i>"It was a year without a Santa Claus</i>

04:51.024 --> 04:54.358
<i>"A Christmas year so sad</i>

04:54.528 --> 04:58.829
<i>"It was a year without a Santa Claus</i>

04:59.132 --> 05:03.626
<i>"The worst we've ever had"</i>

05:10.811 --> 05:14.145
<i>But can you imagine, more or less,
what happened...</i>

05:14.414 --> 05:16.348
<i>...when that news reached the press?</i>

05:16.783 --> 05:19.616
<i>Headlines screamed, wires were humming.</i>

05:19.820 --> 05:23.415
<i>"Santa says, 'Too tired, not coming.â€œ</i>

05:24.825 --> 05:30.025
<i>Out in the stable nuzzling hay,
the reindeer dreamed of Christmas day.</i>

05:30.530 --> 05:33.329
<i>But Santa phoned the reindeer groom.</i>

05:34.334 --> 05:37.861
<i>Hang up the harness in the big storeroom.</i>

05:38.071 --> 05:40.802
He called to his elves
and he told each gnome:

05:40.907 --> 05:44.741
Cover up the shelves. We're...

05:45.979 --> 05:47.242
<i>...staying home.</i>

05:47.514 --> 05:49.608
What? Cover the shelves?

05:49.983 --> 05:51.815
<i>...cried the gnomes and elves.</i>

05:52.552 --> 05:53.747
Cover the dolls?

05:53.820 --> 05:55.083
And electric trains?

05:55.222 --> 05:57.816
And the rocking horses
with shaggy manes?

05:58.058 --> 06:00.925
And the rubber boots
for splashing in parks?

06:01.027 --> 06:02.495
And the cowboy suits?

06:02.829 --> 06:04.319
And the Noah's Arks?

06:05.332 --> 06:06.822
And the Noah's Arks.

06:07.534 --> 06:09.093
And the animals too.

06:12.172 --> 06:12.900
Hello?

06:12.973 --> 06:16.068
Jingle Bells. Number One Elf speaking.

06:16.443 --> 06:18.104
And Jangle Bells.

06:18.445 --> 06:20.174
Will you stop that?

06:20.580 --> 06:22.571
May I ask who is calling, please?

06:23.350 --> 06:26.877
Hi, Mrs. Claus! Yes, Mrs. Claus.

06:27.254 --> 06:28.688
Okay, Mrs. Claus.

06:28.755 --> 06:31.986
Sure thing, Mrs. Claus.
Right away, Mrs. Claus.

06:32.592 --> 06:33.821
Who was that?

06:33.894 --> 06:34.918
That was...

06:35.295 --> 06:36.592
Come on.

06:39.499 --> 06:42.434
It fits. It fits very nicely.

06:44.537 --> 06:46.631
I bet I could be Santa Claus.

06:47.941 --> 06:52.003
"Who would know the difference
if Santa Claus was me

06:52.979 --> 06:55.209
"Yes, who would know the difference

06:55.415 --> 06:58.680
"Just Santa Claus and me

07:03.356 --> 07:06.519
"Anyone can be Santa

07:07.027 --> 07:09.962
"Why can't a lady like me

07:10.664 --> 07:14.601
"I admit, I'm underfed
but with a pillow from the bed

07:14.901 --> 07:17.131
"I could be Santa Claus

07:18.638 --> 07:22.074
"Anyone can play Santa

07:22.475 --> 07:25.172
"I fantasized it a lot

07:26.079 --> 07:30.016
"With this hat upon my head
and his suit of Christmas red

07:30.350 --> 07:33.376
"I could be Santa Claus

07:33.787 --> 07:37.314
"And with his, 'ho, ho, ho' I'd be going

07:37.958 --> 07:40.518
"Down the chimneys with his sack

07:41.962 --> 07:45.489
"And although my curls may be showing

07:45.932 --> 07:49.061
"I'll make sure they only see me
from the back

07:49.903 --> 07:53.498
"Yes, anyone can be Santa

07:53.873 --> 07:57.332
"A tantalizing remark

07:57.877 --> 08:01.905
"Though his boots are not my size
with a twinkle in my eyes

08:02.282 --> 08:05.047
"I could be Santa Claus

08:13.927 --> 08:17.522
"With his reindeer and his sleigh
I'd be up, up and away

08:17.664 --> 08:20.292
"Yes, I could be Santa

08:20.400 --> 08:22.266
"I could be Santa

08:22.469 --> 08:26.804
"I could be Santa Claus"

08:30.343 --> 08:31.902
Santa, you changed your mind.

08:31.978 --> 08:33.946
Oh, joy! Oh, happy day!

08:36.349 --> 08:38.215
Well, boys, what do you think?

08:38.585 --> 08:39.881
Hi, Mrs. C.

08:39.953 --> 08:41.852
Mrs. C!

08:43.123 --> 08:44.522
No good, huh?

08:44.724 --> 08:47.625
I guess we'll have to move
right on then to plan B.

08:47.827 --> 08:48.760
Plan B?

08:48.828 --> 08:49.761
What's that?

08:50.330 --> 08:54.164
As I see it, Santa doesn't want to go
because nobody cares, right?

08:54.234 --> 08:54.962
Right.

08:55.035 --> 08:58.562
He thinks there's no Christmas spirit,
no goodwill. Right?

08:58.838 --> 08:59.634
Right.

08:59.706 --> 09:03.836
So, all you have to do is go down there
and find some example...

09:03.910 --> 09:06.538
...of Christmas spirit left over
from last year.

09:07.213 --> 09:10.274
Scout up some goodwill
and show him some proof...

09:10.350 --> 09:12.614
...that somebody cares. Right?

09:12.819 --> 09:13.650
Right.

09:13.920 --> 09:17.788
Santa will change his mind,
and presto, Christmas is on again.

09:20.760 --> 09:22.785
Now, make sure you don't get lost.

09:23.563 --> 09:24.860
- Lost?
- Lost?

09:25.298 --> 09:27.630
Vixen's made the trip. Haven't you, dear?

09:28.001 --> 09:30.936
- She'll take you. No problem.
- Yeah, but...

09:31.337 --> 09:35.103
Just hurry along and gather up
enough proof to change Santa's mind...

09:35.208 --> 09:37.677
...and we can get on
with Christmas as usual.

09:39.379 --> 09:42.781
Bon voyage. Send us a card now and then.

09:47.087 --> 09:49.317
I wasn't sure I was doing the right thing.

09:49.389 --> 09:52.620
But faced with the idea of having
no Christmas at all...

09:52.959 --> 09:55.326
...drastic measures were called for.

09:57.864 --> 10:00.890
What's all that racket out there, Ma?

10:02.068 --> 10:06.005
It was just one of the reindeer
getting himself some exercise, dear.

10:06.639 --> 10:09.802
With all the rest
and relaxation around here...

10:09.876 --> 10:12.174
...everybody's jumpy as a leapfrog.

10:12.445 --> 10:15.506
It just isn't natural for this time of year.

10:15.715 --> 10:19.982
They'll get used to it. I have already.

10:20.887 --> 10:24.448
I tell you, this is life.

10:24.924 --> 10:26.688
If you say so, dear.

10:27.227 --> 10:32.063
Are you thinking that I'm doing
the wrong thing by staying home?

10:32.799 --> 10:36.429
Of course not, dear.
But if you should change your mind...

10:36.503 --> 10:39.905
Okay, what are you up to, Ma?

10:40.607 --> 10:42.371
Me? Up to something?

10:43.610 --> 10:44.634
Ridiculous.

10:44.744 --> 10:46.644
Do I look like I'm up to something?

10:46.713 --> 10:49.546
No, you don't look like
you're up to something...

10:49.616 --> 10:53.246
...but whenever you look like
you're not up to anything...

10:54.120 --> 10:55.610
...you're up to something.

10:57.157 --> 10:58.556
What are you up to, Ma?

10:58.625 --> 11:01.492
It's nothing that need concern you.

11:02.095 --> 11:03.494
Poor Jingle.

11:04.264 --> 11:05.459
Poor Jangle.

11:05.765 --> 11:07.699
Jingle! Jangle!

11:07.767 --> 11:10.759
Concern it, Ma. What's going on?

11:11.171 --> 11:13.037
They're only trying to help.

11:13.439 --> 11:14.998
Where are they?

11:15.175 --> 11:17.701
They thought they'd just browse
around the world...

11:17.810 --> 11:21.178
...and see if the folks didn't really care
about you and Christmas.

11:21.247 --> 11:25.150
You mean, they went down there
out into that...

11:25.618 --> 11:28.110
...cruel world by themselves?

11:28.288 --> 11:31.815
Of course not, silly.
Vixen went with them.

11:32.158 --> 11:36.026
Vixen! She's just a baby.

11:38.198 --> 11:40.223
Poor little girl.

11:41.401 --> 11:43.597
No telling what might happen.

11:44.137 --> 11:46.231
Now I'll have to go after them.

11:46.306 --> 11:49.503
Do you think you ought to, dear,
with your cold and all?

11:49.642 --> 11:51.041
I have to go.

11:51.444 --> 11:54.812
Those three won't even get
past the Miser brothers without...

11:54.881 --> 11:57.009
The Miser brothers, oh dear!

11:57.784 --> 11:59.912
I forgot all about those two.

11:59.986 --> 12:02.614
Of all the fool things for them to do.

12:02.689 --> 12:06.683
If Snow Miser doesn't freeze them
just for the fun of it...

12:06.759 --> 12:09.785
...his devil of a brother
will put the heat on them for sure.

12:11.497 --> 12:16.526
Dasher! On the double!

12:17.837 --> 12:21.364
Away, Dasher! Away!

12:24.611 --> 12:27.046
<i>The Miser brothers. What a pair!</i>

12:27.313 --> 12:30.840
<i>Snow Miser, who controls
the northern part of the world...</i>

12:30.917 --> 12:33.147
<i>...trying to turn everything to icicles...</i>

12:33.219 --> 12:36.211
<i>...and his nasty brother
trying to keep the south so hot...</i>

12:36.289 --> 12:38.314
<i>...with nary a snowflake a year.</i>

12:39.058 --> 12:41.425
<i>Thanks to me, Vixen, Jingle and Jangle...</i>

12:41.561 --> 12:43.757
<i>...were headed right between the two.</i>

12:43.863 --> 12:46.195
Where are we? Where are we heading?

12:46.299 --> 12:47.960
What do you think?

12:50.436 --> 12:52.598
Don't just stand there, you fools!

12:52.672 --> 12:55.300
They're part of the Santa Claus gang
of goody-goodies.

12:55.975 --> 12:58.706
They must be on their way
to start everybody grieving...

12:58.778 --> 13:00.439
...about white Christmas again.

13:01.314 --> 13:04.978
Don't let them get through.
Singe their britches for them.

13:07.053 --> 13:07.884
Get them.

13:07.954 --> 13:10.048
Get them!

13:11.157 --> 13:13.489
<i>Of course, I never dreamed
that little Vixen...</i>

13:13.559 --> 13:18.156
<i>...would make the mistake of flying
right smack into Heat Miser's territory.</i>

