13:27.974 --> 13:31.035
They got away. They got away!

13:39.118 --> 13:41.917
<i>Just a baby, perhaps,
but little Vixen pulled the boys...</i>

13:41.988 --> 13:43.581
<i>...out of a pretty tight spot.</i>

13:43.656 --> 13:45.624
I wonder where we are now?

13:45.692 --> 13:48.093
If you ask me, still in serious trouble.

13:48.428 --> 13:49.896
Look! Look down there.

13:50.630 --> 13:52.257
Southtown, U.S.A.

13:52.732 --> 13:56.066
That looks like as good a place as any
to find some Christmas spirit.

13:56.202 --> 13:58.500
Take her down, Vixen old girl.

14:01.841 --> 14:03.536
Where is everybody?

14:03.609 --> 14:05.509
Boy, that's what I'd like to know.

14:05.745 --> 14:09.773
How can we find any goodwill
if we can't even find any people?

14:12.385 --> 14:14.149
All right, buddy, pull over.

14:14.253 --> 14:15.743
What's the problem, Officer?

14:15.822 --> 14:18.757
"What's the problem?"
I'll tell you what the problem is.

14:18.958 --> 14:20.824
Driving a... Riding a...

14:21.661 --> 14:23.527
What do you call that thing anyway?

14:23.730 --> 14:24.856
That's Vixen.

14:25.298 --> 14:28.700
Riding a Vixen the wrong way
on a one-way street...

14:28.835 --> 14:30.428
...crossing the white line...

14:30.636 --> 14:33.799
...and wearing funny-looking suits
on a Sunday.

14:33.873 --> 14:34.738
But--

14:34.874 --> 14:36.672
Tell it to the judge.

14:36.876 --> 14:39.504
Maybe they don't like reindeer
in these parts.

14:39.946 --> 14:43.348
I know what! We'll make her a disguise.
Take your socks off.

14:43.416 --> 14:44.884
Take my socks off!

14:44.951 --> 14:46.316
Just do as you're told.

14:48.588 --> 14:51.057
And there we have "instant Rover."

14:51.357 --> 14:54.554
Now, let's take our dog for a walk...

14:54.627 --> 14:58.291
...and see if we can find
some Christmas spirit and goodwill.

15:00.666 --> 15:01.929
<i>Yoo-hoo, madam.</i>

15:02.001 --> 15:03.366
What do you want?

15:03.469 --> 15:05.961
I wonder if we might speak with you
for a moment.

15:06.339 --> 15:07.966
Do you believe in Santa Claus?

15:08.174 --> 15:11.576
At my age? Who are you?

15:11.778 --> 15:12.870
My name is--

15:12.945 --> 15:15.004
What on earth is that?

15:15.515 --> 15:17.711
That's our little puppy dog, Rover.

15:17.784 --> 15:18.808
A dog?

15:18.885 --> 15:21.684
Yep. Bark for the lady, Rover.

15:29.762 --> 15:32.493
Kitty cat. Kitty, come here.

15:35.935 --> 15:39.633
Yeah, I've seen them. Two little fellas
wearing goofy clothes.

15:40.473 --> 15:43.067
They didn't get into any trouble,
did they, Officer?

15:43.342 --> 15:44.901
I'll say they got in trouble.

15:44.977 --> 15:47.810
Wait until the judge gets finished
with them lawbreakers.

15:47.880 --> 15:49.905
He'll give them what for.

15:51.184 --> 15:54.950
Not much Christmas spirit there,
and just as I feared...

15:55.588 --> 15:57.386
...they're in trouble already.

15:57.857 --> 16:00.189
We better find them quick.
Poor little guys.

16:00.893 --> 16:02.486
Must be scared to death.

16:04.530 --> 16:06.294
I'm scared to death.

16:06.499 --> 16:10.527
Serves you right.
"Bark for the lady, Rover," indeed.

16:11.604 --> 16:14.369
Why don't we just skip the whole business
and go home?

16:14.507 --> 16:17.636
I'd like to, but I hate to let Mrs. C down.

16:17.977 --> 16:22.278
We've just got to find a trace of
Christmas spirit and goodwill somewhere.

16:22.548 --> 16:23.606
I know.

16:23.716 --> 16:27.050
Santa's favorites have always been
the little ones, the children.

16:27.220 --> 16:28.984
Why don't we talk to one of them?

16:29.055 --> 16:30.284
Good idea.

16:31.491 --> 16:33.960
There are a whole bunch
of children over there.

16:34.126 --> 16:36.254
Let's talk to them and get out of here...

16:36.329 --> 16:40.493
...because I think Vixen's coming down
with something. She's got a slight fever.

16:40.766 --> 16:43.895
Poor thing.
She's just not used to this weather.

16:44.103 --> 16:47.869
You just lay down here in the shade, girl.
We'll be right back.

16:49.175 --> 16:52.668
I beg your pardon, young man.
May we have a word with you?

16:52.879 --> 16:57.544
Sure. Hey, they're dressed up
like a couple of Christmas elves.

16:58.451 --> 17:01.819
Haven't you heard the news?
Santa's taking a holiday.

17:01.988 --> 17:03.649
Yeah, it was in all the papers.

17:03.990 --> 17:06.584
Well, you don't seem
to be very upset about it.

17:06.659 --> 17:08.752
Upset? Why should I be upset?

17:08.861 --> 17:10.260
Yeah, what's the big deal?

17:10.363 --> 17:13.094
You mean, you don't care
if Santa Claus comes or not?

17:13.366 --> 17:14.390
None of you?

17:14.467 --> 17:15.957
No.

17:16.368 --> 17:18.736
Of course not. It's none of our business.

17:18.804 --> 17:22.240
Besides, believing in Santa Claus
is for little kids.

17:22.308 --> 17:23.469
Yeah.

17:23.608 --> 17:25.008
This is serious.

17:25.077 --> 17:26.909
It's worse than I thought.

17:27.280 --> 17:31.478
If I were you guys, I wouldn't waste time
worrying about Santa Claus.

17:31.617 --> 17:33.642
You got a bigger problem.

17:33.853 --> 17:35.048
What do you mean?

17:35.488 --> 17:37.320
